      "rationale": "Stiffness: E/uval=0.84, difference=3.2%. Yield force: E/uval=1.12, difference=5.7%. Force at 40 mm: E/uval=1.31, difference=6.9%. All three QoIs satisfy both acceptance criteria across all three FEA implementations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly linked to the clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 specifies these three QoIs as the standard performance endpoints for spinal implant constructs. Construct stiffness relates to load sharing; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement characterize fatigue-relevant structural margins."
    },
